    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41284</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_001&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>ここでふたつの国が
戦争をしてたんだ……</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>So this is where the war between both countries took place...</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>1</SpeakerId>
      <Id>1</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41368</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_002&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>……なんで人は戦争をするのかな</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>...Why do people wage war?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>2</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41440</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_003&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>争いが好きだから？</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Because we enjoy conflict?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>1</SpeakerId>
      <Id>3</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41536</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_004&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>違うよ、大切な何かを
守るために戦うんだよ</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>That's not really true. War sparks when there are very important things that have to be fought for.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>4</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41620</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_005&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>&lt;Rody&gt;さんは
どう思いますか？</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>What do you think about this, Miss &lt;Rody&gt;?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>5</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41724</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_006&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>弱い者は滅び、優秀なものが
残るのがこの世のならい</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>The weak are destroyed while the strong remain...That's the one cruel reality of the world.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>4</SpeakerId>
      <Id>6</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41840</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_007&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>戦って勝った者だけが生き残っていくのが
生物の本能だから、かな</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Only the victors are allowed to leave the battlefield alive. It's in our instinct to fight for our survival. Don't you think?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>4</SpeakerId>
      <Id>7</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>41964</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_008&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>それじゃあ、みんな仲良くってのは
自然の法則に反するってことになるよね</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>So you think that to be in good terms with everyone is against the nature of humanity?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>8</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>42084</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_003_094_009&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>例え、そうだとしても……わたしは、
もっとみんなと仲良くしたいな……</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>That...might be true. After all, we haven't been at peace with everyone we met in this journey...</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>9</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
